]]%0a*[[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TZa--csDsYE|Cry in the Sun]]%0a*[[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X5G9tIe84lE|Everybody Talks]]%0a*[[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F1O-edOOXKI|Trouble Man]]%0a*[[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GsB_cGdgPTo | Crossroads]]%0a*[[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o2q6gQkYkaQ | Carbon]]%0a*[[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xCKRGVQlWkI | Love Me or Leave Me]]%0a----%0a%0a!! Description%0a%25lfloat width=400px margin-top=0px margin-left=0px margin-bottom=5px margin-right=25px%25 https://78.media.tumblr.com/8638baafa399cd74036007d3997c3cc0/tumblr_nzlfllhGCo1tkje4eo3_500.gif%0aTall and slender with a swimmer’s body and a look that screams that he is some ethnic mix that is not native to the area. Dark hair and usually dark eyes, the only strange thing is that from time to time those eyes seem to take on an unearthly, icy blue. What can be seen of his skin is generally always unblemished and smooth, though a bit dark for someone who can pass for white in most company.%0a%0aRemy is often seen wearing clothes that may have gone out of fashion 40 years ago, as of recently, the style of choice has been slacks and a button down dress shirt, with a vest over it all. With either a newsboy cap, fedora, or with no hat at all, Remy tends to turn heads, and knows that he does.  As of late, there's been a little less... glamour to his appearance.  Still beautiful by the standards of most folks, instead of the unaging look of the psychic vampires, he's taken on a much healthier, sturdy look.  Magic looks good on him, and the feelings that surround him when his magic is present seems to only add to the appeal of the man, even if he seems to look more mundanely beautiful than before.%0a%0aFrom time to time, Remy dresses the part of his namesakes, Papa Ghede and Baron Samedi.  Black rough worn slacks, an old piano players tuxedo coat complete with tails, and a top hat with a purple band.  Sometimes there's a bone mask over his face, other times there isn't.  But always, the accent goes deeper, the eyes become more intense.  It's easy to see, when that switch gets flipped, how he was feared in the past as a force to be reckoned with during the War.%0a%0a'+The Art+'%0a%0a'''Back Piece'''%0a%0a*The tombstone is the center piece, flanked by Coffin statues on either side. The top hat hangs on the cross bar of a cross atop the tomb. The background is a swamp at night, trees hanging with skeletal branches that frame the tombstone. The colors are black, with shades of blue and purple to resemble the night sky. The red on the top hat is a bright splash of color on the piece. The edges are ragged and unfinished, adding to the image.%0a%0a'''Right Arm'''%0a%0aOn his upper right arm, there is a stack of gold coins, the ink shows quite some age to the tattoo.%0a%0a'''Left Arm'''%0a%0aOn his upper left arm, there is a hand of cards, Aces over 8s, often called a Dead Man's hand.  The ink shows that it's probably his oldest tattoo.%0a%0a----%0a%0a!! Rumor Has It...%0a%25lfloat width=400px margin-top=0px margin-left=0px margin-bottom=5px margin-right=25px%25 https://thumbs.gfycat.com/MaleReasonableBarbet-max-1mb.gif%0a*Some say that you should be on your best behavior around Remy.  Something about eating souls?%0a*If there's anything magic about him, it's his fingers.%0a*Survived the War of the Four by being more ruthless than any others he came across.%0a*Is in direct competition with all the bar owners of the city.  That's why the drinks are free.%0a*Doesn't actually sell things from the Antique shop, it's a front.  He's independently wealthy.%0a*Is actually really a werewolf.%0a*He may actually be a mass hallucination of the people around him.%0a*Remy destroyed the hold of Maelstrom on an entire group with a single stroke of magic.%0a----%0a%0a!! From the Mouths of the Victors...%0a%0a'+Born on the Bayou+'%0a%0a%25rfloat width=400px%25https://thumbs.gfycat.com/SentimentalHoarseIndianrockpython-max-1mb.gif%0a%0aAsk Remy where he grew up and all he can really say is "N'awlins, Ah guess.".  Unfortunately, he lost most of his memory in a traumatic fight with the one who cursed him with his long living gift of Psychic Vampirism.  While he's starting to remember more and more of his past with meditation and the gifts of others, he's not too open about what he has regained of his memories.  What he does speak of, though, is at complete odds with the man he was during the War, and who he has shown himself to be.%0a%0aRemy grew up dirt poor, in a little shanty out on the bayou.  Dirt floors, wood stoves, and guns that were used for hunting down dinner or defending the house from riffraff who had an issue with the Cajun families living anywhere near polite society.  He doesn't talk of siblings, or his mother and father, just the shack, just the boat, just the Loa.  He was a practitioner of voodoo, with strong connections to Ghede/Baron Samedi, and enjoyed the benefits of such in the small community of practitioners, working and trading with them to survive out in the wilderness.%0a%0a'+Wartime Stories+'%0a%0a%25lfloat width=400px%25https://78.media.tumblr.com/a5d4206ed9793f2f16b38cdefd5a4981/tumblr_mwxwrysgti1qc1s6co3_250.gif%0a''If you would like to have had ties with Remy during the War of the Four, whether as rivals, friends, or acquaintances, please contact me in private.''%0a%0aWhile most people know the happy-go-lucky rogue that is Remy, what few do know is that he most certainly was not always that.  Coming to Portland in the the early 1950s, he stumbled right into the middle of the War of the Four.  As a mortal, and with the Rose City Guild not truly having formed to be the protective shelter that it is now within the city, he was forced to walk a razor's edge to keep himself, and those he cared about safe.%0a%0aWithin two years of coming to town, the Speakeasy was up and running, and Remy was creating a reputation for himself.  Some knew him as the 'Baron', for he walked that fine like between life and death, working with each faction, carefully, only showing force when absolutely needed, and making sure that each show of force was a lesson to at least one of the factions when it was done.  He rarely had an issue with the Wise or the Lost, but the Kindred and the Uratha seemed to take special interest in Remy and his dealings.%0a%0a'+Downtime at the Speakeasy+'%0a%0a%25rfloat width=400px%25https://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mbv25zXlul1r8k3z2.gif%0a%0aThe Speakeasy is truly the one crowning achievement of Remy's, and it's seen it's fair share of use throughout the years.  From the smuggler tunnels that lead around parts of the city to allow access with secret panels, to the shop above it, Remy's taken his time to care for it properly, to the point one would imagine that it was his first love.  Parties, events, meetings, debates, negotiations...  All manner of things occur here, and Remy loves the fact that he can help it happen there.  In ages long gone, the Rose City Guild met there on occasion, a place to discuss things where there were rules, but not laws.  It continues on to this day, with Remy watching over the place and the proceedings with the keen eye of a man who loves the place with all his heart.%0a%0a'+My Eyes are Open...+'%0a%0aIt eventually came to pass that Remy's time as a psychic vampire would come to an end.  Most had thought if anything, he would have wound up as a Vampire, but this was not the fate that had been chosen for him.  Awakening seemed the furthest thing from what could happen, but Awaken he did.  Straight to the path of the Thyrsus. From Death, to Life incarnate.  And so he took the name Ghede...  the Man at the Crossroads, the one who stood vigil between the living, the dead, and even the spirits themselves...  He's made strides in his studies, becoming one of the foremost in Spirit magic in the city, coming up with a few rather nasty tricks that have served him well in the few months since his Awakening.%0a%0a'+A Hate So Real+'%0a%0a----%0a%0a!! Contacts%0a%0a(:table table border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0:)%0a%0a(:cellnr width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.imgur.com/Licu228.jpg%0a[[EssenceCorvin| Essie]] and [[VerbenaPoemLarson| Verbena]]\\%0a%25white%25 Nearly everyone knows that Remy is madly in love with the two women, and he most certainly lavishes all the attention he can on the two of them.%0a%0a(:cell width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.imgur.com/7Vlwq3G.jpg%0a[[CharlieRose | Charlie]]\\%0a%25white%25 She nearly walked out of my life, before she was a part of it.  I asked her stay, she did.  A new journey begins...%0a%0a(:cellnr width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/fox-thegifted/images/f/f2/BTS_1x05_Boxed_In_Emma_Dumont_%2527Magneto_gesture%2527.jpg%0a[[AriaAetherRockefeller | Aria]]\\%0a%25white%25 The two of them met by him giving her a ride home when she had too much to drink.  SInce then, they keep running into each other, all over town.%0a%0a(:cell width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.pinimg.com/736x/b5/ca/ab/b5caabb5261d0bcdb9b5c7bfd9bbc941.jpg%0a[[BillAsmodeusWilliamson | Bill]]\\%0a%25white%25 One of Remy's oldest friends still alive within the city.  The two spent some time working together, to whatever dubious ends they were up to at that point, and have recently become reacquainted.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 http://pre08.deviantart.net/f835/th/pre/i/2016/116/2/9/pharah_doodle_by_monorirogue-da0ah2k.jpg%0a[[VrysSarkhet | Vrys]]\\%0a%25white%25 The two met at a very interesting time in Remy's life, and have become closer and closer with each passing week.  The strangeness of the mix of the spiderling warrior and the Cajun socialite worries some, but to others is a rather normal thing to see of the Cajun and those he keeps close.%0a%0a(:cell width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 http://www.malemodelscene.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Clement-Becq-Brice-Hardelin-Vangardist-05.jpg%0a[[AlanNiKDeckard | NiK]]\\%0a%25white%25 One of the first Awakened faces that Remy sought out on his own.  The two men have become fast friends, talking for hours on end about philosophy and life.%0a%0a(:cellnr width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.pinimg.com/564x/5e/be/70/5ebe70c4416c6a2dfb1d666facac093e.jpg%0a[[TeganBladesFoster | Zanj Mwen]]\\%0a%25white%25 They have a past.  They're working on the present.  Do they have a future?%0a%0a(:cell width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.imgur.com/HAwa3nf.jpg%0a[[LoreleiBowen | Lorelei]]\\%0a%25white%25 Remy has a soft spot a mile long for Lorelei, and it shows in the way that he drops most things to help her out, if she needs it.  Very good friends indeed.%0a%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a!! Hooks%0a%0a%25rfloat width=400px%25https://78.media.tumblr.com/a7f44908fbb4a22386c39dcf6fb748df/tumblr_mxz28llgs41sgqffyo2_250.gif%0a*Lets go Antiquing- Remy runs Darbonne Antiques, and is always on the lookout for a new deal. Buying or selling, he’s your man.%0a*Veteran of the War- Those with the age to know may vaguely remember him from his days during the War of the Four, or possibly you think it was his grandfather, as he doesn’t look a day over 25. He has the look though, that makes veterans think of the fact that he may have been there, for better or worse.%0a*Recently Awoken- As confusing as he ever was, Remy is no longer what he once was.  Now a member of the Awakened, he looks at the world through new eyes.%0a*Undercity- Remy's been spending more and more time in the Undercity, making connections, gaining a following.  Want to get involved?  He and [[Charlie Rose|Charlie]] are good people to speak to.%0a%0a----%0a%0a!! Quotes%0a%0a%25lfloat width=350px margin-top=0px margin-left=0px margin-bottom=5px margin-right=25px%25https://i.gifer.com/M0Tn.gif%0a%0a%0a*"The first thing most people might see is a modern day Dionysus.  But once you get past that you would find a lost soul making his way amidst the chaos.  He's a veritable ocean calm.  Giving, yet wild and stormy."- [[AriaAetherRockefeller |Aria]]%0a%0a*"It was a mistake from the start, but I still have the key." - [[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=19xGDxYZQiQ|The Girl With The Key]]%0a%0a*"Ah be knownin' ya names, Papa Ghede... Baron Samedi... Horned God... an' tha one Ah seem ta have fahgo'en... but Ah be knowin' tha' one too... So you be given me a good word when it my turn to see ole' Semitaire... What else ah friends foh..." - [[AlanNiKDeckard|NiK]]%0a%0a*"It would be so easy, but I think I would just wind up hating both of us." - [[TeganBladesFoster|Zanj Mwen]]%0a%0a*"Sometimes the hardest thing we will ever do in life, is to just live it.  Even if we don't want to anymore.." - [[Charlie Rose|Lottie]]%0a%0a*"Love is not a mere emotion, it is a state of being. A living breathing thing that means nothing without a heartbeat to keep it going. You are my heartbeat." - [[Verbena Poem Larson|VB]]
