rything not fundamentally human. Is this true -- and if so, where does he draw the line between what is "human" and what is not?%0a> * Has an elusive mentor and a well-tended library on subjects esoteric and occult. What drives this thirst for knowledge? %0a84,102c55,60%0a%3c !! From the Mouths of the Victors...%0a%3c %0a%3c '+Born on the Bayou+'%0a%3c %0a%3c Ask Remy where he grew up and all he can really say is "N'awlins, Ah guess.".  Unfortunately, he lost most of his memory in a traumatic fight with the one who cursed him with his long living gift of Psychic Vampirism.  While he's starting to remember more and more of his past with meditation and the gifts of others, he's not too open about what he has regained of his memories.  What he does speak of, though, is at complete odds with the man he was during the War, and who he has shown himself to be.%0a%3c %0a%3c Remy grew up dirt poor, in a little shanty out on the bayou.  Dirt floors, wood stoves, and guns that were used for hunting down dinner or defending the house from riffraff who had an issue with the Cajun families living anywhere near polite society.  He doesn't talk of siblings, or his mother and father, just the shack, just the boat, just the Loa.  He was a practitioner of voodoo, with strong connections to Ghede/Baron Samedi, and enjoyed the benefits of such in the small community of practitioners, working and trading with them to survive out in the wilderness.%0a%3c %0a%3c '+Wartime Stories+'%0a%3c %0a%3c ''If you would like to have had ties with Remy during the War of the Four, whether as rivals, friends, or acquaintances, please contact me in private.''%0a%3c %0a%3c While most people know the happy-go-lucky rogue that is Remy, what few do know is that he most certainly was not always that.  Coming to Portland in the the early 1950s, he stumbled right into the middle of the War of the Four.  As a mortal, and with the Rose City Guild not truly having formed to be the protective shelter that it is now within the city, he was forced to walk a razor's edge to keep himself, and those he cared about safe.%0a%3c %0a%3c Within two years of coming to town, the Speakeasy was up and running, and Remy was creating a reputation for himself.  Some knew him as the 'Baron', for he walked that fine like between life and death, working with each faction, carefully, only showing force when absolutely needed, and making sure that each show of force was a lesson to at least one of the factions when it was done.  He rarely had an issue with the Wise or the Lost, but the Kindred and the Uratha seemed to take special interest in Remy and his dealings.%0a%3c %0a%3c '+Downtime at the Speakeasy+'%0a%3c %0a%3c The Speakeasy is truly the one crowning achievement of Remy's, and it's seen it's fair share of use throughout the years.  From the smuggler tunnels that lead around parts of the city to allow access with secret panels, to the shop above it, Remy's taken his time to care for it properly, to the point one would imagine that it was his first love.  Parties, events, meetings, debates, negotiations...  All manner of things occur here, and Remy loves the fact that he can help it happen there.  In ages long gone, the Rose City Guild met there on occasion, a place to discuss things where there were rules, but not laws.  It continues on to this day, with Remy watching over the place and the proceedings with the keen eye of a man who loves the place with all his heart.%0a---%0a> !! Hooks%0a> %0a> * Big Game Hunting - chances are, if you're looking to hunt anything supernatural, Eric will gladly join you. If only the word "hunt" was less open to interpretation...%0a> * Make New Friends, But Keep the Old - Eric is growing increasingly adept at contacting the deceased. If you're missing a loved one who died, or if you're just after a secret someone took to their grave, ask Eric what you can do about that...%0a> * Always Be Learning - Eric knows people who know people in Academia. His connections in the sphere of learning are potentially vast, and ever-growing. There's always something more to learn, and Eric can help you find the perfect teacher. He personally loves to teach others, too. %0a> * Around the Block - Eric is not newly Awakened. He is a self-proclaimed "slow bloomer," but despite his relatively long Awakening, he is a surprisingly quick learner. He'll trade for knowledge. %0a105,153d62%0a%3c !! Contacts%0a%3c %0a%3c (:table table border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:cellnr width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.imgur.com/Licu228.jpg%0a%3c [[EssenceCorvin| Essie]] and [[VerbenaPoemLarson| Verbena]]\\%0a%3c %25white%25 Nearly everyone knows that Remy is madly in love with the two women, and he most certainly lavishes all the attention he can on the two of them.%0a%3c %0a%3c (:cell width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.imgur.com/HAwa3nf.jpg%0a%3c [[LoreleiBowen | Lorelei]]\\%0a%3c %25white%25 Remy has a soft spot a mile long for Lorelei, and it shows in the way that he drops most things to help her out, if she needs it.  Very good friends indeed.%0a%3c %0a%3c (:cellnr width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/fox-thegifted/images/f/f2/BTS_1x05_Boxed_In_Emma_Dumont_%2527Magneto_gesture%2527.jpg%0a%3c [[AriaAetherRockefeller | Aria]]\\%0a%3c %25white%25 The two of them met by him giving her a ride home when she had too much to drink.  SInce then, they keep running into each other, all over town.%0a%3c %0a%3c (:cell width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.pinimg.com/736x/b5/ca/ab/b5caabb5261d0bcdb9b5c7bfd9bbc941.jpg%0a%3c [[BillAsmodeusWilliamson | Bill]]\\%0a%3c %25white%25 One of Remy's oldest friends still alive within the city.  The two spent some time working together, to whatever dubious ends they were up to at that point, and have recently become reacquainted.%0a%3c %0a%3c (:cellnr width=360px:) %25lfloat width=150%25 https://i.pinimg.com/originals/92/a4/9e/92a49ef1894e0