lly always unblemished and smooth, though a bit dark for someone who can pass for white in most company.%0a%3c %0a%3c Remy is often seen wearing clothes that may have gone out of fashion 40 years ago, as of recently, the style of choice has been slacks and a button down dress shirt, with a vest over it all. With either a newsboy cap, fedora, or with no hat at all, Remy tends to turn heads, and knows that he does.%0a%3c %0a%3c '+The Art+'%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Back Piece'''%0a%3c %0a%3c *The tombstone is the center piece, flanked by Coffin statues on either side. The top hat hangs on the cross bar of a cross atop the tomb. The background is a swamp at night, trees hanging with skeletal branches that frame the tombstone. The colors are black, with shades of blue and purple to resemble the night sky. The red on the top hat is a bright splash of color on the piece. The edges are ragged and unfinished, adding to the image.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Right Arm'''%0a%3c %0a%3c On his upper right arm, there is a stack of gold coins, the ink shows quite some age to the tattoo.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Left Arm'''%0a%3c %0a%3c On his upper left arm, there is a hand of cards, Aces over 8s, often called a Dead Man's hand.  The ink shows that it's probably his oldest tattoo.%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !! Rumor Has It...%0a%3c %0a%3c *Some say that you should be on your best behavior around Remy.  Something about eating souls?%0a%3c *If there's anything magic about him, it's his fingers.%0a%3c *Survived the War of the Four by being more ruthless than any others he came across.%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !! From the Mouths of the Victors...%0a%3c %0a%3c '+Born on the Bayou+'%0a%3c %0a%3c Ask Remy where he grew up and all he can really say is "N'awlins, Ah guess.".  Unfortunately, he lost most of his memory in a traumatic fight with the one who cursed him with his long living gift of Psychic Vampirism.  While he's starting to remember more and more of his past with meditation and the gifts of others, he's 